&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Gruve&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gruve is an innovative software services startup dedicated to transforming enterprises to AI powerhouses. We specialize in cybersecurity, customer experience, cloud infrastructure, and advanced technologies such as Large Language Models (LLMs). Our mission is to assist our customers in their business strategies utilizing their data to make more intelligent decisions. As a well-funded early-stage startup, Gruve offers a dynamic environment with strong customer and partner networks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated Business Analyst / AI Project Lead to drive AI-led transformation initiatives across Enterprise IT Infrastructure. The ideal candidate will bridge business and technology teams, analyze business needs, manage cross-functional projects, and identify opportunities to leverage AI and automation for improving operational efficiency.&amp;nbsp;This role requires strong business acumen, excellent stakeholder management skills, and a solid understanding of Enterprise IT Infrastructure, Cloud, Networking, and AI technologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather, analyze, and document business requirements from internal and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business requirements into functional specifications, user stories, and process workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead AI and Digital Transformation initiatives across Enterprise IT Infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities for process optimization using Generative AI, AI Agents, and workflow automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Infrastructure, Cloud, Networking, Security, Product, and Engineering teams for successful project execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare business cases, solution proposals, executive presentations, and project documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage project timelines, scope, risks, dependencies, and stakeholder communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define project KPIs and track delivery against business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Agile ceremonies, sprint planning, backlog prioritization, and UAT activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze business processes and recommend technology-driven improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay updated on emerging AI technologies and industry best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Basic Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Engineering (B.E./B.Tech) in Computer Science, Information Technology, Electronics &amp;amp; Communication, or a related engineering discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full-time, two-year MBA from a recognized university or premier business school.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience as a Business Analyst, AI Project Lead, Technology Consultant, Product Analyst, or similar role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience working on Enterprise IT Infrastructure, Cloud, Networking, Cybersecurity, or Digital Transformation projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC), Agile/Scrum methodologies, and Business Analysis practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical, problem-solving, communication, and stakeholder management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with AI/Generative AI solutions, including LLMs, AI Agents, Microsoft Copilot, ChatGPT, Azure OpenAI, or similar technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Enterprise IT Infrastructure, Cloud Platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP), Networking, Cybersecurity, and IT Service Management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Jira, Confluence, Azure DevOps, ServiceNo

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Gruve&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gruve is an innovative software services startup dedicated to transforming enterprises to AI powerhouses. We specialize in cybersecurity, customer experience, cloud infrastructure, and advanced technologies such as Large Language Models (LLMs). Our mission is to assist our customers in their business strategies utilizing their data to make more intelligent decisions. As a well-funded early-stage startup, Gruve offers a dynamic environment with strong customer and partner networks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gruve is hiring an on-site engineer to plan, test, and deploy OS and software patches across Windows-based devices and connected instruments at our client Pune facility. This is a regulated, engineering-led environment where careful testing and change control matter as much as the patching itself. Daily on-site presence is required, with occasional after-hours maintenance windows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan, test, and deploy OS/software patches and security updates to Windows devices and instruments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize patches by risk and severity (CVE/CVSS); maintain compliance against SLAs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test before production rollout and execute rollback plans to protect critical systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate maintenance windows with Client&#39;s IT and instrument owners; work within change-control processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot patch failures and maintain accurate device/patch inventory and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Basic Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelors in computer science /IT/Engineering or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years in IT/Engineering with hands-on Windows OS and Software Patch-Management experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong with current and legacy/embedded Windows (10/11, Server, Win 7, Win 10 IoT).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with patch tools (SCCM/MECM, WSUS, Intune; Ivanti/Tanium/BigFix a plus) and vulnerability management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working alongside engineering/lab environments; change-management awareness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and oral communication; professional, client-facing demeanor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work on-site in Pune full-time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience patching lab/diagnostic/medical devices; regulated-environment exposure (GxP, 21 CFR Part 11); PowerShell scripting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Gruve&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Gruve, we foster a culture of innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone can thrive and contribute their best work. If you’re passionate about technology and eager to make an impact, we’d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gruve is an equal opportunity employer. We welcome applicants from all backgrounds and thank all who apply; however, only those selected for an interview will be contacted.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Gruve&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gruve is an innovative software services startup dedicated to transforming enterprises to AI powerhouses. We specialize in cybersecurity, customer experience, cloud infrastructure, and advanced technologies such as Large Language Models (LLMs). Our mission is to assist our customers in their business strategies utilizing their data to make more intelligent decisions. As a well-funded early-stage startup, Gruve offers a dynamic environment with strong customer and partner networks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position summary: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Infrastructure Security Engineer for Device Management Team, having 5+ years of experience in Device Management. The team member will be responsible for the administration of the Security Devices like Next Gen Firewall.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Roles &amp;amp; Responsibilities: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Firewall Operations &amp;amp; Troubleshooting:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor, manage, and optimize firewall performance, health, and security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform advanced troubleshooting of firewall-related issues, working closely with L1 and L2 teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate security incidents, network anomalies, and connectivity issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fine-tune firewall rules, policies, and configurations for performance and security improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on packet captures and traffic analysis to diagnose network security issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rule &amp;amp; Policy Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, implement, and modify firewall rules while ensuring security and compliance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct firewall rule audits and remove redundant or obsolete rules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage access control policies, VPN configurations, and segmentation policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with organizational and regulatory security guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Incident &amp;amp; Change Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as an escalation point for L1 engineers and assist in resolving complex firewall issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in Root Cause Analysis (RCA) for recurring firewall incidents and recommend fixes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle firewall upgrades, patches, and firmware updates as per change management procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support IT security and compliance teams in conducting risk assessments and vulnerability remediation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAU Operations &amp;amp; Automation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement automation scripts for firewall monitoring and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize firewall logging, alerting, and monitoring for proactive security management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with vendors and OEM support teams for hardware/software troubleshooting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation &amp;amp; Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain up-to-date documentation on firewall configurations, rule changes, and security incidents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare reports on firewall performance, threat activities, and policy violations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide training and mentorship to L1 engineers on firewall best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in IT, Computer Science, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant security/network certifications such as &lt;strong&gt;Cisco FTD/FMC&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;CCNP Security, Fortinet NSE 3+, Palo Alto PCNSA/PCNSE, Check Point CCSA/CCSE, Juniper JNCIS-S

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Gruve&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gruve is an innovative software services startup dedicated to transforming enterprises to AI powerhouses. We specialize in cybersecurity, customer experience, cloud infrastructure, and advanced technologies such as Large Language Models (LLMs). Our mission is to assist our customers in their business strategies utilizing their data to make more intelligent decisions. As a well-funded early-stage startup, Gruve offers a dynamic environment with strong customer and partner networks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location - Navi Mumbai, India&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly skilled&lt;strong&gt; Infrastructure Security Engineer-L2&lt;/strong&gt; (Palo Alto &amp;amp; NGFW)&amp;nbsp;responsible for implementation, administration, and support of &lt;strong&gt;Palo Alto Next-Generation Firewalls (NGFW)&lt;/strong&gt; across enterprise and cloud environments. The role involves handling &lt;strong&gt;day-to-day operations, incident management, troubleshooting, and TAC coordination&lt;/strong&gt;, along with contributing to firewall migrations and security enhancements. The engineer will play a key role in maintaining secure and stable network infrastructure for critical business operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide &lt;strong&gt;L2 support&lt;/strong&gt; for Palo Alto NGFW environments, including incident handling, troubleshooting, and resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage &lt;strong&gt;day-to-day firewall operations&lt;/strong&gt;, including policy changes, NAT configurations, and VPN management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform &lt;strong&gt;advanced troubleshooting&lt;/strong&gt; for network and security issues across on-prem and cloud environments (AWS, Azure, GCP, OCI).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle &lt;strong&gt;TAC coordination&lt;/strong&gt; with vendors for critical and complex issues.&lt;/li&gt;
